<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by Ragon der Magier on 10-06-2000 12:08 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[i]&gt;&gt;As for Tut's interface ideas. It's quite similar actually, except for the right mouse thing. We're trying to keep that one real simple in that it only does two things :

-Cast a spell
-Close a plate&lt;&lt;[/i]

And that압 a big mistake IMHO!

Your using the mouse as your primary interface tool and can only take the minimum of two buttons into account.
So w/ packing almost every possible option onto the left one and leave the other one to just spell casting and plate closing (what the heck are those "plates" btw?), seems very unbalanced and waste of potential in my eyes - as long as testing proves opposite.
I mean, for Diablo it may be ok, but w/  :div:압 sheer load of options?!?
Left is overloaded and right underused.

Tut압 ideas appear much more reasonable to me, though:
Dividing left=movement control and right=use options
 :up: :up: :up: Tut!

What i dislike is the R key for running mode toggle:
1. Any option that압 "hidden" in this messy letter key area is a pain
2. Why not using the arrow up/down keys for ac-/deceleration? Or the +/- keys from the Numpad?
3. What i miss is a third movement speed: where압 [i]sneaking mode[/i]???

I agree that item pick up via left drag is a reasonable compromise. The benefit of avoiding interferences w/ fighting/movement issues counts more than a slight loss of convenience IMHO.
The method isn앖 so uncomfortable anyway as it is quite similar to the usual way files are put into the recycling bin for deletion under [i]Windows[/i].

Hotkey assignment: Why not via the &lt;shift&gt;+&lt;hotkey&gt; quite known i guess from [i]AoE[/i]?
The range is sufficient.

Pause game: Why is an icon obligate? Use the &lt;Pause&gt; key, what else anyway? ;)

Movement: "Left drag = walk in direction"
Somehow i tend not to get this. Wouldn앖 "Left drag = follow mouse" the more precise formulation?
Maybe i앐 just nitpicking... :)

Strg: Using this as a "manual override" for performing unusual actions like item destruction is a clever and intuitive idea.  :up:

drag object on enemies: i like your idea for throwing bombs, potions, stones etc. very much, Tut!  :up:
Lar: Make it so!  ;)

[i]&gt;&gt;click on doors&lt;&lt;[/i]
I thought doors open automatically when trying to walk through? (unless locked, then -&gt; right click=lockpick/use key ;))

[i]&gt;&gt;combat mode toggling&lt;&lt;[/i]
Hmm, didn앖 you have a key for drawing/put back weapon? Why not linking this together?
Would seem just logical to me...

[i]&gt;&gt;under the barrel&lt;&lt;[/i]
Well it should of course not be highlighted, as it압 only accessible after removing the barrel anyways.

Yours Ragon

P.S.: Thanx Lar btw for the insight into "the development of your development"! ;) :D</TEXTAREA>
